NEW PAINT + NEW STAINLESS APPLIANCES

This 2 level END UNIT  townhome offers a spacious open floor plan and is in immaculate condition. Main floor features living room with fireplace, dining room, kitchen and plenty of cabinet space as well as a .50 bath. Upper level has a  good size loft area perfect for an office or sitting room, full size laundry, master bedroom with double windows- walk in closet and full bath with jacuzzi tub. Two car attached garage. Nice patio.  Tenant pays : Gas, electric, water as well as cable, internet and phone.

About Burnsville: Situated on the south bank of the Minnesota River, Burnsville is just minutes from the MSP International Airport and major regional attractions like Mall of America, Valleyfair, the Minnesota Zoo, and Canterbury Racetrack and Card Casino. Popular shopping areas include Burnsville Center and Heart of the City which includes urban-style retail, restaurants and condominiums. Presentations at the Burnsville Performing Arts Center entertain and educate with cultural events, dramas, comedies, dance and musical acts from local arts organizations and national touring artists. It is also home to the Dakota Valley Symphony. There are over 24,000 housing units in Burnsville. Right on the state average, 32 percent are occupied by renters. The median rent is $940 per month. Burnsville is served by the Burnsville-Eagan-Savage ISD 191, and parts of Burnsville are also served by the Rosemount-Apple Valley-Eagan ISD 196, honored with six National Blue Ribbon Schools of Excellence awards. It does NOT matter if you have bad credit, bankruptcy, late payments, judgements, liens, tax problems or charge offs, you can still buy one of our homes. It doesn't matter if you have verifiable income. We believe that everyone has a right to own their own home. Here is how we do it. We sell the property "Rent to Buy". That means you will be buying the property for a specific period of time, usually 1-2 years depending on your situation. And during that time you have the option to buy it at the price that was agreed upon when you first move in. You will also pay a "Lease Option Fee" when you move in and buy the house. This money will apply to the purchase price of the home and will reduce (usually eliminate) the down payment when you eventually take out a 30 year mortgage with a bank.

Lease Term12 Month minimum

PROPERTY DESCRIPTION
15353 Greenhaven Lane Unit 104 Burnsville, MN 55306 Burnsville Rental Property 4602, 2BR 2BR townhome with spacious open floor plan. Main level features living room with fireplace, dining room, .50 bath and kitchen. Upstairs you will find both bedrooms, full bath, and laundry. Both bedrooms are nice and large {14x14 and 14x11}. Lawn care and snow removal as well as trash are included in the rent. Tenant pays gas, electric, and water as well as cable, internet and phone if desired. Negotiable on one cat with additional $500 pet deposit +$25.00 per month pet rent. Convenient location to shopping-Burnsville Center, restaurants, Buck Hill skiing, as well as 35W. Nice outdoor patio as well as attached one car garage. About Burnsville: Situated on the south bank of the Minnesota River, Burnsville is just minutes from the MSP International Airport and major regional attractions like Mall of America, Valleyfair, the Minnesota Zoo, and Canterbury Racetrack and Card Casino. Popular shopping areas include Burnsville Center and Heart of the City which includes urban-style retail, restaurants and condominiums. Presentations at the Burnsville Performing Arts Center entertain and educate with cultural events, dramas, comedies, dance and musical acts from local arts organizations and national touring artists. It is also home to the Dakota Valley Symphony. There are over 24,000 housing units in Burnsville. Right on the state average, 32 percent are occupied by renters. The median rent is $940 per month. Burnsville is served by the Burnsville-Eagan-Savage ISD 191, and parts of Burnsville are also served by the Rosemount-Apple Valley-Eagan ISD 196, honored with six National Blue Ribbon Schools of Excellence awards. The Burnsville Transit Station serves as the hub and headquarters of the Minnesota Valley Transit Authority, providing regional bus service to five other suburbs. Application fee $50.00 per adult/ $55.00 out state.
